comments: The Spanish entry in the Eurovision Song Contest 1983, performed in Spanish by flamenco singer Remedios Amaya. Her performance of the song on stage in Munich, singing with the traditional Spanish 'cantaora' technique and dancing barefoot, was at the time described by BBC commentator Terry Wogan as "tempestuous" and "very, very ethnic indeed". The song was performed 7th on the night, following Turkey's Çetin Alp and The Short Waves with "Opera" and preceding the Switzerland's Mariella Farré with "Io cosi non ci sto". At the close of voting, it had received 0 points, placing 19th (equal last) in a field of 20.
